course.subject: ELEC
course.name: Final Year Project in Entrepreneurship
course.description: Each undergraduate student taking the Entrepreneurship Option of the Electronic Engineering program is required to complete a final year project before graduation. The project will have significant focus on starting new companies, improving manufacturing process, project management, meeting requirements of existing standards, and marketing strategy. It will be led by faculty members with startup and management experiences to provide first hand training to these students. The credit load will be spread over 3 terms.
